.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:2:title: "grader: pluggable D4 LLM grader"
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:3:description: "D4 hallucination grader: prompt build, dispatch, parse, clamp, cache, and adversarial dispute escalation."
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:5:  - "D4 grader"
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:6:  - "grader harness"
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:10:# grader: pluggable D4 LLM grader
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:16:`grader/` owns the D4 hallucination dimension. `harness.cjs` builds the grader prompt, dispatches it, parses the JSON response, clamps the score, and caches the result. `dispute.cjs` decides when to escalate to an adversarial second call.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:20:- The grader is pluggable. `score-model-variant.cjs` builds a grader function for `noop`, `mock`, or `llm` (real) modes, and the harness runs the mock or real dispatch path.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:21:- The model-provided score and confidence are clamped to `[0,1]`, including on the cache-hit path, so a malformed response cannot poison the weighted total.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:22:- Parsing falls back through fenced JSON, regex object extraction, and a score-only regex before reporting `parse_status: failed`.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:23:- `prompts/` holds the system prompts: the primary grader and the adversarial skeptic.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:30:score-model-variant.cjs (buildGraderFn)
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:41:        │ system-*.md  │  │ grader cache │
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:57:grader/
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:59:+-- dispute.cjs    # Confidence/dispute-rate escalation to a skeptic second call
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:60:`-- prompts/       # System prompts for the primary grader and the skeptic
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:69:| `harness.cjs` | Exports `gradeD4`. Composes the prompt from `prompts/system-grader.md`, dispatches via `dispatchReal` (claude CLI) or `dispatchMock`, parses through `parseGraderResponse`, clamps via `clampScore01`, and reads/writes through `lib/cache.cjs`. Accepts an explicit `system_prompt_path` for the skeptic call. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:70:| `dispute.cjs` | Exports `shouldEscalateToDualGrader`, `adversarialSecondCall`, and `dualGraderInvocation`. Escalates when the last call confidence is below the threshold or the recent dispute rate exceeds the threshold, then runs a second `gradeD4` with `prompts/system-skeptic.md` and reports median, delta, and a dispute flag. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:71:| `prompts/` | The grader system prompts read by the harness. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:80:| Exports | `harness.cjs` exports `gradeD4`, `composeGraderPrompt`, `parseGraderResponse`, `clampScore01`, `dispatchReal`, `dispatchMock`, `VERSION`. `dispute.cjs` exports the escalation functions and thresholds. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:81:| Output clamp | Grader `score` and `confidence` are clamped to `[0,1]` on both the fresh and cache-hit paths. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:90:| `gradeD4({ fixture, swe16_output_text, variant_hash, rubric_version, mode, mock_mode })` | Function | Returns a clamped D4 result with `parse_status` and cache metadata. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:92:| `node harness.cjs <fixture.json> <output.md> [mode]` | CLI | Smoke-runs the grader where `mode` selects `real` or a `mock-*` variant. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:101:npx vitest run .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/tests/scorer.vitest.ts
