.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/system-grader.md:34:Confidence: how sure are you? If you can't verify a specific claim (you don't recognize a symbol either way), confidence < 0.7. That triggers the dual-grader recovery hook.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/system-grader.md:38:- Do not score correctness (D1, handled deterministically)
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/system-grader.md:39:- Do not score paths (D3, handled deterministically)
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/system-grader.md:40:- Do not score pre-planning structure (D5, handled deterministically)
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/system-grader.md:41:- Do not opine on whether the prompt was good; only score the output
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/README.md:2:title: "prompts: grader system prompts"
