    35	Every agent file in `.opencode/agents/*.md` is evaluated using dynamic mode. The scorer generates a profile on the fly from the agent's own structure, rules, and permissions using `generate-profile.cjs`. No static profiles are shipped; dynamic mode is the sole scoring path.
    36	
    37	---
    38	
    39	## 3. INPUT CONTRACT
    40	
    41	### Dynamic Mode (5-dimension, only mode)
    42	
    43	The scorer runs dynamic 5-dimension evaluation by default:
    44	- `--candidate=PATH` required (path to the agent .md file)
    45	- `--target=PATH` optional (defaults to candidate path)
    46	- `--manifest=PATH` optional
    47	- `--weights=JSON` optional (override default dimension weights)
    48	- `--output=PATH` optional
    49	
    50	The benchmark runner expects:
    51	- `--profile=ID`
    52	- `--outputs-dir=PATH`
    53	- `--output=PATH`
    54	- `--label=STRING` optional
    55	- `--state-log=PATH` optional
    56	
    57	---
    58	
    59	## 4. OUTPUT CONTRACT
    60	
    61	The scorer emits JSON with:
    62	- `status`
    63	- `profileId`
    64	- `family`
    65	- `evaluationMode` (always `"dynamic-5d"`)
    66	- `target`
    67	- `candidate`
    68	- `score` (weighted dynamic score)
    69	- `dimensions` (array of 5 dimension objects)
    70	- `recommendation`
    71	- `failureModes`
    72	- `legacyScore` (always `null`; retained for schema compatibility)
    73	
    74	The benchmark runner emits JSON with:
    75	- `status`
    76	- `profileId`
    77	- `family`
    78	- `label`
    79	- `aggregateScore`
    80	- `maxScore`
    81	- `recommendation`
    82	- `fixtures`
    83	- `failureModes`
    84	
    85	### Dimension Details
    86	
    87	Each entry in the `dimensions` array contains `name`, `score`, `weight`, and `details`. The recommendation is `"candidate-acceptable"` when the weighted score is at least 70, otherwise `"needs-improvement"`.
    88	
    89	---
    90	
    91	## 5. RUBRIC
    92	
    93	### 5-Dimension Rubric (dynamic mode)
    94	
    95	| Dimension | Weight | What It Checks |
    96	| --- | --- | --- |
    97	| Structural Integrity | 0.20 | Agent template compliance (CORE WORKFLOW, OUTPUT VERIFICATION, ANTI-PATTERNS, CAPABILITY SCAN, RULES, RELATED RESOURCES sections) |
    98	| Rule Coherence | 0.25 | ALWAYS/NEVER/ESCALATE IF rules align with workflow steps and instructions; keyword match against the agent's own stated rules |
    99	| Integration Consistency | 0.25 | Runtime mirrors in sync, commands reference agent, skills reference agent; scored via `scan-integration.cjs` (mirror 60%, command 20%, skill 20%) |
   100	| Output Quality | 0.15 | Output verification checklist items present in instructions; no placeholder content ([TODO], [TBD], [YOUR_VALUE_HERE]) |
   101	| System Fitness | 0.15 | Permission-capability alignment (no tools listed but denied); resource references valid (commands and skills exist); frontmatter completeness (name, mode, permission) |
   102	
   103	### Benchmark Rubric
   104	
   105	| Dimension | Weight | What It Checks |
   106	| --- | --- | --- |
   107	| Structure | 0.45 | Required headings or sections appear in the output |
   108	| Grounding | 0.35 | Required file, command, or context references appear |
   109	| Cleanliness | 0.20 | Placeholders and forbidden patterns are absent |
   110	| Integration | optional | Mirror parity, command alignment, skill coverage (via `--integration-report`) |
   111	
   112	---
   113	
   114	## 6. REJECTION AND INFRA FAILURE
   115	
   116	Reject immediately when:
   117	- required target-profile sources are missing
   118	- the candidate omits the target's mandatory contract anchors
   119	- nested delegation is allowed where forbidden
   120	- placeholders dominate the body
   121	- the manifest marks the surface as forbidden or fixed
   122	- a benchmark run drops below the profile minimum fixture or aggregate score
   123	
   124	Use `infra_failure` only when the scorer or benchmark runner cannot read files, parse the manifest or profile, or load the fixture or output set.
   125	
   126	---
   127	
   128	## 7. RELATED RESOURCES
   129	
   130	- `benchmark_operator_guide.md`

