.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/gpt55/iterations/iteration-002.md:654:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/research.md:263:| **candidate-source** | agent `.md` candidate | model variant | **the skill-under-test** (SKILL.md + references + RESOURCE_MAP) + the fixture corpus (public/private) |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/gpt55/iterations/iteration-002.md:655:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/research.md:264:| **dispatcher** | — | `dispatch-model.cjs` (5 executors) | **same dispatcher** + decontamination pre-pass + "must emit tool log" + advisor-brief strip + Mode A/B |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/gpt55/iterations/iteration-002.md:656:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/research.md:265:| **scorer** | 5-dim agent rubric | model grader | **new `skill-benchmark` scorer** computing D1–D5; calls `advisor_recommend`/`advisor_validate` out-of-band for D1 |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/gpt55/iterations/iteration-002.md:657:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/research.md:267:Net-new surface is small and named: a **parser** (`parse-resource-loads.cjs`), a **scorer** (`skill-benchmark`), the **fixture split** (`fixtures/<id>.prompt.txt` + `fixtures/<id>.expected.json`), and a **report contract** under `assets/skill-benchmark/` (`report_schema.json`, `report_template.md`, `remediation_taxonomy.json`). Keep the default agent-improvement path byte-identical (Lane B's identity-gate precedent) `[opus/i2 F9][gpt55/i4 #1][minimax/i4]`. **Advisory/non-mutating by default** — emit report + handoff JSON; Lane A receives findings as candidate evidence, does not auto-apply `[minimax/i4 #4][opus/i4 F6]`.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/gpt55/iterations/iteration-002.md:658:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/research.md:273:**Phase gate:** Phase 002 (rename) before Phase 003 (Lane C build) — unanimous. Operational surface ≈ 12–18 files; bulk of the 1063 raw occurrences is immutable history to **exclude**.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/gpt55/iterations/iteration-002.md:659:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/research.md:277:| A | **Canonical skill package** | `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/` (65+ files); `SKILL.md` `name:`/triggers/keywords; README, feature_catalog (~15 pages), manual_testing_playbook (~35 files), references/shared/*, scripts/** READMEs + `.cjs`/`.vitest.ts`, assets/**, changelog, own `graph-metadata.json` | `git mv` then content-sweep moved tree | path refs self-heal via `git mv`; **internal content + `name:` frontmatter survive** and must be swept |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/gpt55/iterations/iteration-002.md:660:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/research.md:278:| B | **Commands + YAML** | `commands/deep/start-agent-improvement-loop.md`, `start-model-benchmark-loop.md`; 4 YAML assets (`*_auto.yaml`, `*_confirm.yaml`) — `skill:` field + ~18 script-path refs each | bulk find/replace (~90 edits); **keep command verbs** | YAML `skill:` stale → command fails to resolve skill at runtime |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/gpt55/iterations/iteration-002.md:661:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/research.md:279:| C | **4 runtime mirrors** | `.opencode/agents/deep-agent-improvement.md`, `.claude/…md`, `.gemini/…md`, `.codex/…toml` (verify TOML `name` key); 3× `README.txt`; `.codex/config.toml` | rename files + content in **one changeset** | rename dir but not mirrors → `skill deep-agent-improvement not found` on every `/deep:start-…` |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/gpt55/iterations/iteration-002.md:662:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/research.md:280:| D | **Skill-advisor (highest risk)** | TS `aliases.ts:27-32` (key + 4 aliases), `explicit.ts:116-138` (~10 boosts + ~7 negative penalties), `fusion.ts`; Python `skill_advisor.py:250` + `:1577-1790` (35+ phrase entries); `skill-graph.json`; `regression_cases.jsonl:42-45`; `native-scorer.vitest.ts`; `system-skill-advisor/graph-metadata.json:70-73` (enhances edge) | update TS+Python **atomically**; regenerate graph; update fixtures; `advisor_rebuild`+`advisor_validate` | split-brain (TS≠Python); negative penalties go **inert** → degraded Lane-A/B disambiguation |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/gpt55/iterations/iteration-002.md:663:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/research.md:289:**Decision-record items for Phase 002:** agent identity (`@deep-agent-improvement` → `@deep-improvement`?); `deep-model-benchmark` alias fate; command verbs (keep — consensus); narrow vs wide `agent-improvement`-token-family scope (wide touches `agent-improvement-state.jsonl` + continuity readers → own sub-packet); backward-compat alias window vs hard cutover.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/gpt55/iterations/iteration-002.md:664:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/research.md:291:**Safe ordering:** see §2/RQ6 (alias-bridge, freeze inventory, git mv + sweep, mirrors lockstep, scope decision, advisor atomic + cross-skill, **regenerate indexes LAST**, validate gate, bridge teardown).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/gpt55/iterations/iteration-002.md:665:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/research.md:295:## 5. Cross-Model Observations (this sweep doubles as a model comparison)
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/gpt55/iterations/iteration-002.md:666:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/research.md:299:- **Opus — deepest first-hand repo grounding; the synthesizer's source of record.** Only model to read the advisor scorer internals (`advisor_scorer.md`: the 5-lane weights, 0.72 derived-cap, 0.05 ambiguity margin), `validation_baselines.md` (80.5%/77.5% corpus/holdout), `evaluator_contract.md`, and the *shipped* 121 deep-review report. Produced the highest-leverage unique findings: the **5-stage funnel**, the **concrete `dynamic profiling`≠`dynamic profile` substring bug**, the **two-capture-mode** design, **canary tokens**, the **advisor-brief in-context leak**, the **T1↔T2 circularity meter**, the **runQuality block**, and **stamp-root-and-auto-invalidate** for rename. Weakness: **web was permission-gated**, so all RQ7 prior art is `[web-unverified]` (needs later confirmation); highest raw census (1063) without the active/immutable split DeepSeek made cleaner.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/gpt55/iterations/iteration-002.md:667:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/research.md:301:- **GPT-5.5 — best spec-anchoring + harness engineering discipline.** Uniquely tied weights to the parent spec's own R1–R5 (25/25/20/15/15) rather than inventing them. Strongest on harness *engineering* (public/private split, OpenTelemetry span model, `normalizedResourceId`, hallucinated-path defense). Three-sub-score activation (added `activationOutcome`). Owner-grouped 7-family taxonomy with the richest per-finding field set (`ownerSurface`/`suggestedPatchTarget`/`verificationCommand`/`handoffLane`). The hard-gate-above-weighted-list ranking formula.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/gpt55/iterations/iteration-002.md:668:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/research.md:304:**Convergence quality:** RQ3 (both sub-scores), RQ2 (public/private split + contamination gate + log-parse capture), RQ5 (dual artifact + hard gate + owner-specific taxonomy + Lane A handoff), and RQ6 (rename-before-build + advisor paired-representation risk + regenerate-indexes-last) are **strong 4-model (or 3-model for RQ2) consensus** — high confidence. The one genuine divergence is **D1–D5 weights**, and even there the cluster is tight (D3=0.15 unanimous; disagreement only on the routing-vs-usefulness lead).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-implementation-deep-research/research/gpt55/iterations/iteration-002.md:669:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/research.md:306:**Where a single model is load-bearing (verify before building):** the advisor 5-lane reuse, the 0.72 derived-cap, and the `dynamic profiling` bug are **Opus-only** first-hand claims — high-value but should be re-confirmed against `advisor_scorer.md` + `deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:12,119` during Phase 003 (Opus itself flagged the `triggers:` vs `trigger_phrases:` frontmatter-key projection as unverified). The "production traffic from skill-graph SQLite as gold fixtures" path is **MiniMax-only** and depends on MCP query access that may be a Phase-003 infra prerequisite.
